programme.title: Most Haunted: Aldwych Underground Station

programme.title: Most Haunted: Michelam Priory
programme.desc: Michelam Priory was originally a church built on a medieval moated island. In 1556 it was transformed into a house where many families have lived through history and tragedy.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Station Hotel, Dudley
programme.desc: The team returns to Dudley, this time to investigate the Station Hotel. Since its opening in 1910, the hotel has welcomed many famous guests, but is said to be haunted by the ghost of a murdered maid.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Derby

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Last Assignment

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Bind the Wounds

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Heaven on Earth

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summit

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Torch
programme.desc: Tragedy occurs when a Neo-Nazi disputes the Holocaust with the son of a death camp survivor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Sail Away

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Laura Hammond
programme.desc: 34 year old Laura Hammond has a body to die for. Her stomach is flat; her slim legs go all the way up to her chin and she's got the sassy ass of a super model. According to a poll of 100 Mancunians, this young woman looks like a 48 year old!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding Her Hidden Value
programme.desc: Tracy is a real estate appraiser who can't seem to find the value in her looks. She works in a man's world where her clothes are usually more butch than beautiful. With a new job starting soon, Tracy needs to re-vamp her look fast.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Officer Hottie
programme.desc: Rosario is Mr. Mom by day and a New York City police officer by night. He spends his life outdoors which has done a number on his skin while his massive dental issues have done a number on his wallet. We're going to try to make him look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Very Tall Order
programme.desc: This part-time model traded in her big city lifestyle for a family in the suburbs. Mylene's appearance has taken a backseat to her kids and full-time job. She needs a team of experts to update her look and give her a quick shot of confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hippie To Happening
programme.desc: Albert loves traveling and trying new things, except when it comes to his appearance. Albert's bad divorce has left him feeling self-conscious about the lines on his face and his graying, thinning hair.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp "One Year On"

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom
programme.desc: Dawn designs swimming pools and home-schools her daughter, but this can-do mom can't take time for herself. Cosmetic dentistry and high-tech dermatology remove the visible effects of stress, and the Glam Squad brings her inner beauty to the surface.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in the Limelight

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team battles to save a man trapped in his overturned Land Rover on Rakino Island; a star rugby player at Onewhero may have broken his neck after a scrum collapsed, and a man out cycling on Waiheke is clinging to life after a cardiac arrest.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5

programme.title: Paranormal State: Night Terrors
programme.desc: Ryan leads his team to one of the most haunted places in the US to confront their fears and solve a paranormal mystery. Aside from the alleged spirits of dead prisoners, something even darker may be lurking inside West Virginia State Penitentiary.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Get Out of This House
programme.desc: When an aggressive spirit stalks a young family, PRS is called in to investigate. When it is determined that the source of the haunting may have been unknowingly invited in, Ryan races to identify and hopefully defeat the entity before it's too late.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Darkness Falls
programme.desc: Ryan leads his team to one of the most haunted places in the US to confront their fears and solve a paranormal mystery. Aside from the alleged spirits of dead prisoners, something even darker may be lurking inside West Virginia State Penitentiary.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Paranormal Detour
programme.desc: With time off between cases, Ryan suggests to the PRS team they choose a random town to investigate. They roll into St. Helens, Oregon, home of Twilight, where they learn about the long history of the paranormal in the area.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Messenger
programme.desc: Kelli and her husband Riley are frightened in their coastal Oregon home. They are plagued by a headless apparition and often hear mysterious noises that resemble cries for help from the dark corners of their house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Asylum
programme.desc: PRS explores a New York State Prison that was once a mental asylum. Ryan and his team go behind bars to uncover the institution's paranormal past and present.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Boy Pushed Me
programme.desc: Bruce and Danielle are terrified by an EVP recorded in their Indiana home stating "Kill them." Even more chilling, their toddler son survived a fall out of a window only to tell his parents, "Boy pushed me."

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Haunted Piano
programme.desc: Ryan and the PRS team are called in when unlucky antique collectors unwittingly bring a paranormally-infested piano into their home. The team attempts to dismantle and destroy the offending instrument.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Supernatural Seduction
programme.desc: PRS investigates the Campbell House, where the Innkeeper and guests claim to have sexual encounters with a spirit who has deep ties to a family tragedy.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Drowned
programme.desc: Kim and her family have been frightened out of their seaside Maryland home. Multiple family members have reported sightings of children with purple lips and strange noises emanating from the nearby creek.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Spirits of the Slave Dungeon
programme.desc: Ryan books a two-night case in a real haunted jail in Charleston, SC, but PRS soon realizes the spirits themselves are being held there against their will and subjected to an unjust form of torture.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Requiem
programme.desc: A young woman named Kristy has been haunted in her own bedroom since she can remember. Now it's up to Ryan and the crew to help Kristy before she's overwhelmed by the entity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Knickerbocker
programme.desc: PRS checks into the Knickerbocker Hotel in Linesville, Pennsylvania where the owners are reporting strange noises and the appearance of phantom children in some of the rooms.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Beer, Wine and Spirits
programme.desc: Brian's bar has a cranky customer who's got a bad habit of breaking wine glasses. Charlie has been dead since prohibition.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Llancaiach Fawr, Wales
programme.desc: The team investigates a 15th-century manor that has been renovated to its original glory. It's said to be haunted by many of its previous occupants including soldiers, children and a maid.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Clock House, Surrey
programme.desc: Part one of the Ruth Ellis ghost mystery. The team meets demonologist Fred Batt at his impressive home. Derek detects the presence of a woman called "Ruth" that leads to the team's next investigation.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Pengersick Castle, Cornwall
programme.desc: This ancient and crumbling castle invokes the troubled maritime and smuggling history of Cornwall. This is an atmospheric location that spooks even the hard-bitten Most Haunted crew.

programme.title: Most Haunted: RAF East Kirkby
programme.desc: The "Most Haunted" team visits the Lincolnshire Aviation Heritage Centre. There, they investigate reports of ghostly pilots who have returned after being killed during World War II.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Edinburgh Vaults
programme.desc: The 19 arches beneath Edinburgh's South Bridge were turned into underground vaults housing unsavory characters. Body snatchers Burke and Hare are believed to have operated there. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Leith Hall
programme.desc: Murders, strange noises and an apparition of a wounded soldier take the team to Leith Hall. Grey mists, eerie music and the spectral image of a white lady all lie in wait for the "Most Haunted" team.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aberglasney House
programme.desc: Multiple deaths, a curse and many hauntings draw the "Most Haunted" team to the bizarre Aberglasney House in Wales.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 1

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 2

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: For the Love of Larry
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark rescue victims trapped in a car, thanks to a helpful dog.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: That's Our Dad

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 24-Hour Makeover

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Picture Perfect

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Carolyne Robinson
programme.desc: Mother of four Carolyne Robinson has found domestic bliss to be something of an oxymoron. Fiona McDonald and her team of experts are charged with turning Caroline into a fashionable mum and they have just 10 days to do it.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Kicking Out The Old Look
programme.desc: Janet, a hard-bodied kick boxer, is on round two of her life. A bad marriage had her on the ropes, but she has come back strong and is a college freshman with a new fiancé and wants a face to match her young heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Liz O'Reilly
programme.desc: Bedford deputy newspaper editor, Liz O'Reilly, 40, has some stories to tell and a lifetime of sun, stress and smoking means they're mostly written on her face. Presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand to crack the whip.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Dolled Up
programme.desc: Sara is a lady with a rough medical history who is still able to maintain a heart of gold. After helping her ailing grandmother for many years and conquering a litany of illness herself, Sara and the Glam Squad are ready to update her look.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Taryn Couper
programme.desc: Taryn Couper admits she's stuck in the 1970s so it's up to Fiona McDonald and her team of experts to turn her from Hamilton hippie to boho chic, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Lorraine Harvey
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team take on the challenge of Lorraine Harvey from Tunbridge Wells.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Under New Management
programme.desc: Victoria is a mom and apartment manager without any personal time. Her job creates a lack of structure for her to spend with her family. The Ten Years Younger team will brighten her smile, revive her appearance and open her eyes to new possibilities.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Nicki Hall
programme.desc: Nicki Hall wears her hardships on her face and she's aging quickly. But trying to dress sporty like her teenage daughters just makes her look older. This week Fiona McDonald and a team of experts help turn Nicky into the young woman she is at heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Unstick The 80s

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: You Can't Outrun The Sun

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Deconstructing Mike

programme.title: Wild At Heart

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Timothy Peart’s Last Dance

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Magic Bullet

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key
programme.desc: When a pregnant mother and her two young sons are brutally slain, pressure mounts for the CSPD to catch the cold-blooded monster who did it.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder in a Bottle
programme.desc: Eric Houston is found stabbed to death in a seedy motel, but the ensuing investigation is stymied by a long list of suspects. Lt. Joe Kenda deploys a groundbreaking new technology to catch the killer.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: My, My, Merry Christmas

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes of a Child
programme.desc: A loving, churchgoing grandmother is found stabbed to death in her apartment, leaving Joe Kenda to wonder what sort of monster could do such a thing.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Sex, Lies, and Surveillance Tape
programme.desc: A confrontation between enemies turns deadly, and Lt. Joe Kenda’s best hope for answers lies with a grainy, dubbed-over surveillance tape.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Argonaut & Patches
programme.desc: A family is afraid of being bit by their aggressive English bulldog/Lab mix. Cesar prescribes pack therapy. A Cocker Spaniel has a life-threatening appetite for paper products.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Red Zone
programme.desc: Two new sibling dogs fight over everything, from food to toys. Facing the possibility of giving up one of the pooches, Cesar travels south to end the civil war between the two dueling pit bulls.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bodhi, Maggie & Molly, and Bojo
programme.desc: Bloodhound/Catahoula mix, Bojo, is aggressive when it comes to mealtime. Molly and Maggie, two territorial Maltese, and a Kerry Blue Terrier in need of some calm assertive energy.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Eton & Dolly, and the Pups on Parole
programme.desc: Cesar goes to jail to help wayward humans rehabilitate wayward pups through a program called "Pups on Parole."; Bulldogs learn to play fair.
programme.sub-title: Eton & Dolly, and the Pups on Parole

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lotus Blossoms
programme.desc: A jealous dachshund learns to get along with both of his owners. Can Cesar exorcize a demon possessed German Shepherd that prevents his people from entering certain rooms of the house.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Anti-Social Sasha
programme.desc: Sasha, a pound pup, is perfect in the house, but outside she shows aggression towards other dogs. Angler, a Lab, is blind, and exhibits strange behavior around food.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Joe, and Penny, Roxy, Rico, Lou, & Solomon, and Promise
programme.desc: An Australian shepherd is so devoted to his owner that he breaks leashes to be with her; a neurotic beagle makes trouble for a pack of foster dogs; and an Italian mastiff puppy fears riding in cars.
programme.sub-title: Joe, and Penny, Roxy, Rico, Lou, & Solomon, and Promise

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Hair Puller/Shoe Fanatic
programme.desc: Showcases a woman addicted to shoes, while another is addicted to pulling her hair and eating the follicle.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Couch Cushion/Furry
programme.desc: While battling her addiction to eating couch cushions, Adele has destroyed 7 couches and 2 chairs. Meanwhile, Lauren is more comfortable in her fur suit than in her own skin.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Ventriloquist/Cat Lady
programme.desc: April's addiction to her puppets has gotten so strong she can't go anywhere without them. Debbie is severely allergic to cats, but has over twenty of them, leaving her in isolation.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Can’t Stop Cleaning/Love Rocks
programme.desc: Cyntrelle dropped out of high school because of her addiction to cleaning. Belinda's obsession with rocks has taken over her life, with more than 100,000 scattered around her home.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: East Glass/Bleaches Skin
programme.desc: Josh has eaten more than 250 light bulbs. But is he really addicted to the attention that he receives? Candice thinks dark skin is ugly and has resorted to using dangerous bleaching creams.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Make-up Addict/Obsessed with Death
programme.desc: Maureen won't go out of the house without a full face of makeup. Meanwhile, Barbara is so obsessed with death that she's planned her own funeral.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Laxatives and Pottery/Ashes
programme.desc: Kimberly takes hundreds of laxatives a day in an attempt to lose weight. Meanwhile, Bianca prefers to eat pottery and cigarette ashes instead of food.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Wears Diapers/Eats Dryer Sheets
programme.desc: For Riley, there's nothing like the comfort of wearing a warm, wet diaper. She lives as an adult baby to escape the stresses of life. And Charmissa chews on dryer sheets for up to 10 hours a day.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Rampant Rats/Extreme Fingernails
programme.desc: Theresa has more than 60 pet hairless rats that are taking over her apartment. Jazz has been growing her fingernails for 22 years. Her longest nail is two feet long, and she calls them her children.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession
programme.desc: For more than 30 years, Theresa has been addicted to smelling gasoline. Meanwhile, former drug-addict Krista has 12 'children' -- all of which are teddy bears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2
programme.desc: In this one-hour special, we revisit six of our addicts whose stories shocked the world. Tune in for exclusive never before seen footage in this special episode.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger
programme.desc: Bertha has been drinking up to five bottles of nail polish every day for the past five years but her family is worried she's doing permanent damage to her health. Jamie can't stop digging in her ears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict
programme.desc: Nathaniel has been in a relationship with his car for nearly five years, taking it out on dates, buying it gifts, and even getting intimate with it. Jaye has been addicted to snorting baby powder.
programme.sub-title: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Moose Mount Cabins
programme.desc: Ernie came to Alaska over twenty years ago to hunt, and he's passed that love of hunting to his wife and kids. They have a cabin with no running water and electricity, but they want an upgrade.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Alaska Man Caves
programme.desc: Dan Miotke, a fireman living with his wife and two daughters in Homer, Alaska, is taking the idea of a man cave to a new level, looking for a cheap property that he can fix up into his own man cabin.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Winter Wanderland
programme.desc: Jason and Alana want a home built for the harsh snows of the Mat-Su Valley. Will they take a hunting cabin filled with animal heads, one crafted for the Alaskan sun, or one needing rehab?

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Hooked On A Lake
programme.desc: Life on an Alaskan lake is what Steve and Peg want, in the wilderness of the Mat-Su Valley - a secluded place where, even in the long, harsh Alaskan winters, fish teem beneath the frozen ice.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Snow Machines & Bear Attacks
programme.desc: Newlyweds Garret and Noelle want a remote home in the Alaskan wilderness that’s so off-the-grid, there’s no road leading to it. In the winter, they’ll have to travel by snowmobile.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Ruff-Ing It
programme.desc: Pete and Anja want to buy an Alaskan home that’s right for them AND their 21 dogs. They care more about making their Alaskan Huskies comfortable than they do about themselves.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Baby On Board
programme.desc: Matt and Jessica have a new baby. They want to move into a new home near the ocean around Juneau, Alaska. But waterfront homes are too expensive, so they choose a liveaboard boat!

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Isolated Village
programme.desc: Sean and Jolene want a home in the Alaskan village of Gustavus, where the wildlife runs rampant. There are no roads in or out of town and it’s so remote the bears feel free to walk into your house!

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Mrs. Alaska & Military Man
programme.desc: Pat Harrigan is a soldier, newly stationed at the army base in Fairbanks, Alaska. His wife Rocky just won the crown as the current Mrs. Alaska, but she’s a city girl at heart.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Fish Out Of Water
programme.desc: Grant and Khrissy just got engaged. He’s all-Alaskan but she’s a fish out of water from the Deep South. The couple wants to buy a house that’s a mix of the Alaskan bush and her Alabama roots.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Outhouse Life
programme.desc: Sean and Charlotte want a home in Fairbanks, Alaska, that won’t cost them a penny in utility bills. So they’re going off-the-grid. And that means one thing… there’ll be no bathrooms.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Hangar Homes
programme.desc: Born and bred Alaskans Andy and Nicole grew up in a town so remote, their family vehicles were airplanes! Now that they’re looking for a new home, they need an airplane hangar and a runway.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Remote Coves
programme.desc: Charlie and Toni are outdoor adventure junkies who want a home in Alaska that’s so remote they can catch their next meal from the ocean right off their front porch.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Homer Bound
programme.desc: Nathan and Lindsay are brand new to Alaska. They want a house similar to where Nathan’s pioneer grandfather lived, in the bayside town of Homer, surrounded by the great outdoors.
